# Git Workflow

**NEVER use `git rebase`** on any branch.

## Submodule Workflow (gv2_firmware)

**Developing in submodule:**
```bash
cd gv2_firmware
git checkout -b feature/your-feature
# Make changes, test
git add . && git commit -m "Description"
git push -u origin feature/your-feature
cd ..
```

**Update main repo pointer:**
```bash
git add gv2_firmware
git commit -m "Update gv2_firmware to feature/your-feature"
git push origin feature/uart-to-i2c
```

**Co-worker syncs submodule:**
```bash
git pull origin main
git submodule update
```

**Merge submodule branch to gv2_firmware main, then update pointer in parent repo before merging to main.**
